## NTC <a name="6"></a>
Semiconductor
de coeficiente
negativo.
Resistencia
disminuye al
subir temp:
$$R(T) = R_0 \cdot e^{B \cdot \left( \frac{1}{T} - \frac{1}{T_0} \right)}$$
donde:
* $$R_0$$
  a $$25$$
  grados
  Celsius
  $$^\circ\text{C}$$
  es $$3000$$
  ohmios
  $$\Omega$$
  ($$9795$$
  ohmios
  $$\Omega$$
  a $$0$$
  grados
  Celsius
  $$^\circ\text{C}$$
  ).
* $$B$$
  coeficiente
  $$3925$$
  kelvin
  $$\text{K}$$
* $$T_0$$
  es $$273$$
  kelvin
  $$\text{K}$$
* $$T$$
  temperatura
  en kelvin
  $$\text{K}$$

